main event: A housewife observed a brightly lit, oval-shaped object moving rapidly and silently in the sky over Wichita, Kansas on June 6, 1967.
interesting points: The object appeared to be approximately 1000 feet in altitude and moved in a southerly direction.
Another witness reported seeing a bright light in the sky that appeared to be descending behind some trees.
An unidentified flying object, described as round, silver in color, and approximately 80-100 feet in diameter, was observed hovering over Wichita, Kansas on June 11, 1967.
The object was observed for about 20 minutes before suddenly accelerating and disappearing at a high rate of speed.
Several blurry and indistinct photographs of outdoor scenes and potential UFO sightings were included in the report.
sighted object: brightly lit oval-shaped object, round silver object
photographs: yes, the report includes several blurry photographs
